Student -- tCHAPTER 9. The Perceived Impact of Intercultural Awareness on Peer Interaction: Study of a UK University -- tCHAPTER 10. The Development of Intercultural Competencies During a Stay Abroad: Does Cultural Distance Matter? -- tEngaging Student Diversity -- tCHAPTER 11. Cultivating Voter Participation among First-Generation College Students: The Relationship of Study Abroad Participation to Post-College Voting Behaviour -- tEncouraging Entrepreneurial Spirit among Students -- tCHAPTER 12. Developing Students’ Innovation Capacities: A Comparison between US and Germany -- tConclusion: The ‘Three Cs’ in Practice -- tCHAPTER 13. The Virtues of Cooperation, Complementarity and Competition in Higher Education in Time of Crisis -- tList of Contributors -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe thirteen papers in this collection address three aspects of higher education, primarily in Europe but also in the United States. These aspects are competition, collaboration, and complementarity, both on the level of policy and on the practical level of impact on students and staff. Competition, especially for funding, occurs between and within institutions. Collaboration, more than a basic code of conduct, has become a political principle across Europe. Complementarity in the market for higher education facilitates this collaboration. The themes and contexts in higher education for which the three Cs are examined include missions and identities, response to external forces, the impact of evaluation systems and ranking schemes, the effects of globalisation, intercultural awareness and gender imbalance, and the challenges of student participation. Statistical tables and visual aids support the analysis and arguments. This book is the fifth in a series of publications drawn from the annual Forums of the European Association of Institutional Research (EAIR) from 2013 onwards  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEducation, HigherzEuropevCongresses. 0aEducation, HigherzUnited StatesvCongresses. 7aEDUCATION / Higher.2bisacsh  aAcademic freedom, Education policy, European Union, Gender studies, Higher Education, Ranking.1 aAdekola, Olalekan Adeban, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBehrmann, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBock, Carolin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoonen, Joris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorden, Victor M. H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarvalho, Teresa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCheng, Ming, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCogswell, Cynthia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDegn, Lise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDilmetz, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriedhoff, Caroline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoefnagels, Ankie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJosé Sá, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKobler-Weiß, Michaela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLedermüller, Karl, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLourdes Machado-Taylor, Maria de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMatei, Liviu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMatei, Liviu, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMayhew, Matthew J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.g